companyName: Invesco KBW Property & Casualty Insurance ETF
description:
The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the KBW Nasdaq Property & Casualty Index (the "underlying index").
 The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities of property and casualty insurance companies that comprise the underlying index. It generally invests in all of the securities comprising the underlying index in proportion to their weightings in the underlying index. The fund is non-diversified.
